                    <p>
                      The Skywards Infinite is the ENBD flagship miles card and has been since
                      2019. The proposition is straightforward: spend in AED, earn Skywards Miles,
                      redeem on Emirates flights. The price tag is AED 1,575 a year — or four
                      return economy redemptions to Mumbai, depending how you count it.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      What the marketing copy elides is the earn rate. On UAE-domestic spend the
                      card pays 1 Skywards Mile per AED 4 spent, which on our Skywards valuation
                      works out to roughly 0.6% effective return.
                    </p>
                    <h2>Where the card actually pays</h2>
                    <p>
                      It pays on direct Emirates spend (4 miles/AED), and on overseas non-AED
                      spend after the 1.99% FX fee. The salvage proposition is the welcome bonus
                      and the lounge access.
                    </p>
