                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </WfBoard>

          <WfBoard label="House style guide" width={1280} height={1500}>
            <div class="wf">
              <WfHeader />
              <div class="wf-pagehead">
                <div class="crumb">Internal · for editors</div>
                <h1 style="font-size:56px;">House style.</h1>
                <p>Voice, tokens, and component vocabulary. The point is consistency, not control — when in doubt, write the way you'd brief a sceptical friend at a coffee.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="wf-styleguide">
                <section>
                  <h3>Voice</h3>
                  <div class="vc">
                    <div class="do">
                      <div class="hd">Do</div>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Lead with the verdict.</li>
                        <li>Show your math in AED, with caps and exclusions named explicitly.</li>
                        <li>Concede the obvious counterargument early.</li>
                        <li>Date every claim.</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="dont">
                      <div class="hd">Don't</div>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Use "amazing", "ultimate", "best ever".</li>
                        <li>Quote the marketing brochure as if it were the T&Cs.</li>
                        <li>Mistake high earn rate for high effective value.</li>
                        <li>Hedge in the headline. Hedge in the body if you must.</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </section>
                <section>
                  <h3>Tokens · colour</h3>
