      {/* ─── Editorial pages ──────────────────────────────────────── */}
      <section id="editorial" class="dp-spike-section">
        <header class="dp-spike-section-head">
          <div class="ey">18 · Editorial pages</div>
          <h2>Editorial pages</h2>
          <p>About · Editorial policy · How we make money · Corrections — same template.</p>
        </header>
        <div class="dp-spike-boards">
          <WfBoard label="Editorial · about" width={1280} height={1700}>
            <div class="wf">
              <WfHeader />
              <div class="wf-editorial">
                <div class="crumb">About</div>
                <h1>Why we built DubaiPoints.</h1>
                <p class="lede">We were tired of every UAE points blog being a thinly-disguised affiliate funnel. So we wrote one that isn't.</p>
                <div class="wf-editorial-grid">
                  <h3>Who runs this</h3>
                  <div>
                    <p>DubaiPoints is run by three UAE residents — two writers and an editor — who collectively hold every card we review. We pay our annual fees out of pocket. We do not, and will not, accept advertorial.</p>
                    <p>We've been in the UAE between four and eleven years. Between us we've held accounts at FAB, ENBD, Mashreq, ADCB, HSBC, DIB and ADIB.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="wf-editorial-grid">
                  <h3>Editorial fences</h3>
                  <div>
                    <p>No advertorial. No paid placement. No "sponsored review" labelling — because there are no sponsored reviews. Card-by-card affiliate links exist on this site; they never determine review scores, ranking order, or what gets covered.</p>
                    <p>If we change a verdict — and we have, several times — the previous version stays in the article, struck through, with the date and reason.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="wf-editorial-grid">
                  <h3>How we make money</h3>
                  <div>
                    <p>Three sources, in this order: reader subscriptions to the Friday brief (~31% of revenue), card-application referrals (~58%), and one-off consulting (~11%).</p>
                    <p>The referral percentage is highest because it's easiest to scale; the subscription percentage is the one we want to grow.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="wf-editorial-grid">
                  <h3>Corrections policy</h3>
                  <div>
                    <p>Errors corrected within 24 hours, with a dated note at the bottom. Substantive errors that affect the verdict are corrected immediately, headlined at the top, and emailed to subscribers in the next Friday brief.</p>
                    <p>Submit a correction: <a style="color:#1a5fc6;">info@dubaipoints.ae</a>.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="wf-editorial-grid">
                  <h3>Methodology</h3>
                  <div>
                    <p>Every figure in AED. Every card checked against UAE eligibility rules. Every redemption modelled against DP-value points (not issuer-claimed). Verification dates stamped on each review.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="wf-editorial-grid">
                  <h3>The team</h3>
                  <div class="wf-editorial-team">
                    {[
                      ["Reema A.", "Senior writer"],
                      ["Khalid B.", "Writer"],
                      ["Priya M.", "Editor"],
                    ].map(([nm, role]) => (
                      <div>
                        <div class="ph-img">Portrait</div>
                        <div class="nm">{nm}</div>
                        <div class="role">{role}</div>
                        <div class="bio">Short bio. Years in UAE. Banks held. Specialism.</div>
                      </div>
                    ))}
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <WfFooter />
            </div>
          </WfBoard>
        </div>
      </section>

